    <summary><span data-ttu-id="d81ee-101">針對無法轉換為輸入字元的編碼輸入位元組序列，提供失敗處理機制 (稱為後援)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-101">Provides a failure-handling mechanism, called a fallback, for an encoded input byte sequence that cannot be converted to an input character.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-102">後援會擲回例外狀況，而不會將輸入位元組序列解碼。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-102">The fallback throws an exception instead of decoding the input byte sequence.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-103">這個類別無法被繼承。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-103">This class cannot be inherited.</span></span></summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-104">編碼方式編碼的序列可以傳輸到實體媒體，例如磁碟，或透過通訊連結的位元組序列至對應的 Unicode 字元。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-104">An encoding maps a Unicode character to an encoded sequence of bytes, which can subsequently be transferred to a physical medium, such as a disk, or over a communications link.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-105">字元可以對應以各種方式，而特定的編碼方式由衍生自<xref:System.Text.Encoding>類別。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-105">Characters can be mapped in various ways, and a particular encoding is represented by a type derived from the <xref:System.Text.Encoding> class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-106">具體來說，編碼類型的`GetBytes`方法會編碼成位元組序列的字元和`GetChars`方法解碼為字元的位元組序列。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-106">Specifically, the encoding type's `GetBytes` method encodes a character to a byte sequence, and the `GetChars` method decodes a byte sequence to a character.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-107">如果編碼方式，無法對應輸入的位元組序列解碼作業可能會失敗。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-107">A decoding operation can fail if the input byte sequence cannot be mapped by the encoding.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-108">例如，<xref:System.Text.ASCIIEncoding>物件無法解碼的位元組序列，會產生具有超出範圍 U + 0000 到 U + 007F 字碼指標值的字元。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-108">For example, an <xref:System.Text.ASCIIEncoding> object cannot decode a byte sequence that yields a character having a code point value that is outside the range U+0000 to U+007F.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-109">在無法執行編碼或解碼的轉換的情況下，.NET Framework 提供稱為後援的失敗處理機制。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-109">In cases where an encoding or decoding conversion cannot be performed, the .NET Framework provides a failure-handling mechanism called a fallback.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-110">您的應用程式可以使用預先定義的.NET Framework 解碼器後援，或是建立自訂解碼器後援衍生自<xref:System.Text.DecoderFallback>和<xref:System.Text.DecoderFallbackBuffer>類別。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-110">Your application can use the predefined .NET Framework decoder fallback, or it can create a custom decoder fallback derived from the <xref:System.Text.DecoderFallback> and <xref:System.Text.DecoderFallbackBuffer> classes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-111">.NET Framework 提供兩個預先定義的類別，實作不同的後援策略來處理解碼轉換失敗。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-111">The .NET Framework provides two predefined classes that implement different fallback strategies for handling decoding conversion failures.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-112"><xref:System.Text.DecoderReplacementFallback>類別取代用來取代任何無法轉換的輸入的位元組序列所提供的字串。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-112">The <xref:System.Text.DecoderReplacementFallback> class substitutes a string provided in place of any input byte sequence that cannot be converted.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-113">替代字串，就會發出後，解碼作業會繼續將轉換輸入的其餘部分。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-113">After the substitute string is emitted, the decoding operation continues converting the remainder of the input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d81ee-114">相反地，<xref:System.Text.DecoderExceptionFallback>類別會擲回<xref:System.Text.DecoderFallbackException>時遇到無效的位元組序列。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d81ee-114">In contrast, the <xref:System.Text.DecoderExceptionFallback> class throws a <xref:System.Text.DecoderFallbackException> when an invalid byte sequence is encountered.</span></span>  
  
   
  
